	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The only &quot;issue&quot; with audio_sync.exe I can reproduce is when clicking the application window and/or dragging it around.  Sometimes it doesn't re-synchronise, resulting in never-ending desynchronisation (clicking/stuttering), and the green gradually either decreases (i.e. keeps decreasing indefinitely) or increases and then decreases again indefinitely, etc.. and when I say never-ending, I do mean it -- I've left it running for a few minutes before.  Framerate tends to vary a lot as well (in general though, not during the above), usually somewhere between 59 and 61.  This is on Windows 7 SP1 x64.<br /><br />If A/V evidence of this is needed, can provide, but won't be for a few days.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
